body:
@rabbah, @csantanapr, currently all of the limits/default values are displayed in the controller info route under the limit key. However, I think it would be more organized if the limits were organized in corresponding sections for actions, triggers, packages, etc. See below for examples.

Current format:

```
"limits": {
    "actions_per_minute": 120,
    "action_blocking_timeout": 60,
    "concurrent_actions": 100,
    "activation_poll_record_limit": 200,
    "triggers_per_minute": 60
  }
```

Purposed change:
```
"limits": {
    "actions":
         "invoke": {
              "per_minute": 120,
              "blocking_timeout": 60,
              "concurrent": 100
         }
    },
    "activations": {
         "poll": {
               record_limit": 200
          }
    },
    "triggers": {
         "fire": {
              "per_minute": 60
         }
    }
}
```

